{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "81bbd42e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Practice Questions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6217b49c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "**1. What is the output of the following Qiskit code?**"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "889f4edb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.s(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc_inv = qc.inverse()\n",
    "display(qc_inv.draw('mpl'))\n",
    "\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4f627eba",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A) ![1.png](q_photos/1.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "B) ![2.png](q_photos/2.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "C) ![3.png](q_photos/3.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "D) ![4.png](q_photos/4.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "72ab1459",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "B)
    "Since to inverse the circuit you have to reverse the order and dagger the gates\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0cbdbdcf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "58458ca5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**2. Which method correctly prepares the following state?**\n",
    "$$\n",
    "|\\psi(\\vec{x}^{(1)})\\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{105}}(4|00\\rangle+8|01\\rangle+5|10\\rangle+0|11\\rangle)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "desired_state = [\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 4,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 8,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 5,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 0,\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.initialize(desired_state, [0, 1])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "desired_state = [\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 0,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 5,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 8,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 4,\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.initialize(desired_state, [0, 1])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "desired_state = [\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 0,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 5,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 8,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 4,\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.prepare(desired_state, [0, 1])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "desired_state = [\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 4,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 8,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 5,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 0,\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.prepare(desired_state, [0, 1])\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ba889659",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "desired_state = [\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 4,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 8,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 5,\n",
    "    1 / math.sqrt(105) * 0,\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.initialize(desired_state, [0, 1])\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fcd6a19d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**3. Which classical-data embedding method encodes an $N$-dimensional input into $\\lceil \\log_2 N \\rceil$ qubits?**",
   "id": "37861b995126bea7"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) Basic encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "B) Angle encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "C) Amplitude encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "D) ZZ-feature encoding"
   ],
   "id": "e1d06ff16940fdd5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C) Amplitude encoding\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "59ca1bae045be676"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "d8a4458103548034"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**4. What is the effect of calling `qc.barrier()` on a quantum circuit `qc`?**",
   "id": "86a70cbf45783f57"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) It only adds a visual separator to the circuit.\n",
    "\n",
    "B) It raises an error because `qc.barrier()` requires a qubit register argument.\n",
    "\n",
    "C) It inserts a barrier that prevents the transpiler from reordering or combining gates across that point in the circuit.\n",
    "\n",
    "D) It raises an error because the correct way to add a barrier is `qc.append(barrier())`"
   ],
   "id": "1af7570862dcd2fb"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C) It adds a barrier such that during transpilation gates on each site of the barrier does not get mixed\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "f0265be4fcd23209"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "62e261fb2730b2dc"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**5. Which method of drawing a timeline diagram is correct?**\n",
    "\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization.timeline import draw\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.cx(0,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = transpile(qc, backend, layout_method='trivial')\n",
    "draw(qc)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization.timeline import draw\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.cx(0,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "backend = GenericBackendV2(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = transpile(qc, backend, layout_method='trivial')\n",
    "draw(target=qc, backend=backend.target)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.cx(0,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "backend = GenericBackendV2(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = transpile(qc, backend, layout_method='trivial')\n",
    "qc.draw(method=\"timeline\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization.timeline import draw\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.cx(0,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "backend = GenericBackendV2(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = transpile(qc, backend, layout_method='trivial')\n",
    "draw(qc, target=backend.target)\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "d29e679986917991"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization.timeline import draw\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(2)\n",
    "qc.h(0)\n",
    "qc.cx(0,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "backend = GenericBackendV2(5)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = transpile(qc, backend, layout_method='trivial')\n",
    "draw(qc, target=backend.target)\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "d81fda515423e9cf"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "f511633f0519941a"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**6. Which Qiskit visualization is used to display how logical (virtual) qubits are mapped onto physical qubits of a backend?**",
   "id": "9e017f4d7d782f2b"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) Qsphere visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "B) Gate map visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "C) DAG visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "D) Hinton diagram"
   ],
   "id": "14e66112406ef975"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "B) Gate map visualization\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "6c9b6f090d4ade9e"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "ad67a10c8f2d81eb"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**7. Which of the following Qiskit code snippets correctly defines a single-qubit\n",
    "quantum circuit where the rotation angle $\\theta$ of an RX gate is parameterized\n",
    "by the quadratic expression $\\theta = x^2 + 2x + 1$?**"
   ],
   "id": "d68c7b45bc614247"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "theta = Parameter(\"theta\")\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(theta, 0)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.variational import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(theta, 0)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.variational import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(0, theta)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(theta, 0)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "E)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(0)\n",
    "qc.assign_parameters({rx:theta})\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "79959f7ea3a615da"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "from qiskit.circuit import Parameter\n",
    "\n",
    "x = Parameter(\"x\")\n",
    "theta = x**2 + 2*x +1\n",
    "\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(1)\n",
    "qc.rx(theta, 0)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "401df430ee13cc2"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "427430d657d6d01a"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**8. In Qiskit, which of the following is the correct syntax to apply the sine function to a `Parameter` object named `phi`?**\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "A) `expr = sin(phi)`\n",
    "\n",
    "B) `expr = phi.sin()`\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `expr = apply_sin(phi)`"
   ],
   "id": "8cd73ec96a2bbe45"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "expr = phi.sin()\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "378ff08b001c7f55"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "aeef2338044cf737"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**9. Which of the following Qiskit code snippets correctly transpiles a logical quantum circuit `qc` for execution on a specific physical `backend`?**",
   "id": "d4576c3ff3b8ba1c"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "transpiled_qc = transpile(qc, backend=backend)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "pass_manager = generate_preset_pass_manager(backend=backend)\n",
    "transpiled_qc = pass_manager.transpile(qc)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "pass_manager = generate_preset_pass_manager(backend=backend)\n",
    "transpiled_qc = pass_manager.run(qc)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D) Both A) and B) are correct\n",
    "\n",
    "E) Both A) and C) are correct"
   ],
   "id": "7762ef4cef838cda"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "E) Both A) and C) are correct\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "ce755439e9e528b5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "6b2581fc9714757d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**10. When working with variational quantum circuits that require consecutive executions where each circuit depends on the output of the previous run, which execution method is most appropriate?**\n",
   "id": "da7156a81b78b725"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) Job mode\n",
    "\n",
    "B) Batch mode\n",
    "\n",
    "C) Session mode\n"
   ],
   "id": "54b78ed7fff32f6e"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C) Session mode\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "fd25b26f52b3f002"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "90f024b5c106cbe5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**11. Given a `sampler` instance and a quantum circuit `qc`, how would you submit a job for execution?**\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "A) `job = sampler.run([qc])`\n",
    "\n",
    "B) `job = sampler.execute(qc)`\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `job = sampler.run(qc)`\n",
    "\n",
    "D) `job = qc.run(sampler)`"
   ],
   "id": "3d0d181027498d11"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A) `job = sampler.run([qc])`\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "7d7c4b22c31c10c8"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "d58eb9c7845d877d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**12. What is the correct way to initialize batch mode for a given `backend`?**",
   "id": "23c5807f286ce7c1"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(mode=\"batch\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = sampler.run([qc], mode=\"batch\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(mode=\"batch\", backend=backend)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "batch = Batch(backend=backend)\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(mode=batch)\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "77daa7cd1c1d6eda"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "batch = Batch(backend=backend)\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(mode=batch)\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "61d57628e6b68833"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "6a2c6937cc1241bd"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**13. Which error suppression and error mitigation options are available for the Sampler primitive? Select all that apply.**",
   "id": "91154361969b709d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) Zero-noise estimation\n",
    "\n",
    "B) Pauli Twirling\n",
    "\n",
    "C) Dynamical decoupling\n",
    "\n",
    "D) Twirling Readout Error Extinction (T-REx)\n"
   ],
   "id": "7ac3c26ad8be0c7f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "B) Pauli Twirling and C) Dynamical decoupling\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "e45a8a0fcedb9f76"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "875ff593f9d5173d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**14. Which code snippet correctly submits a quantum circuit `qc` for sampling probabilities on a specified `backend`?**\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = sampler.run([qc])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "job = backend.run(qc, mode=\"sampler\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = sampler.run(qc)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "job = backend.run([qc], mode=\"sampler\")\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "a462a98fbf25f74e"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler = Sampler(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = sampler.run([qc])\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "8ef92b2ba5fa7103"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "fd28fd47d3202e5f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**15. Given a `sampler` instance, how would you enable Pauli Twirling and Dynamical Decoupling options?**",
   "id": "d77a429613c7c24b"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler.twirling = True\n",
    "sampler.dynamical_decoupling = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler.twirling.enable_gates = True\n",
    "sampler.dynamical_decoupling.enable = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler.options.twirling.enable_gates = True\n",
    "sampler.options.dynamical_decoupling.enable = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler.options.twirling = True\n",
    "sampler.options.dynamical_decoupling = True\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "e1e6f061937e7ab2"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "sampler.options.twirling.enable_gates = True\n",
    "sampler.options.dynamical_decoupling.enable = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "eef01e9977272035"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "e8da124abed1dd89"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**16. Which error suppression and error mitigation options are available for the Estimator primitive? Select all that apply.**",
   "id": "499624516ac7937a"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) Zero-noise estimation\n",
    "\n",
    "B) Pauli Twirling\n",
    "\n",
    "C) Dynamical decoupling\n",
    "\n",
    "D) Twirling Readout Error Extinction (T-REx)\n"
   ],
   "id": "4b0b9c21233c2e25"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A), B), C) and D) (All choices)\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "c7c1df087c73c57c"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "a023f2ed004a102f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**17. Which code snippet correctly submits a quantum circuit `qc` for estimating expectation value for `obs` on a specified `backend`?**\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "obs = SparsePauliOp(\"ZZ\")\n",
    "estimator = Estimator(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = estimator.run([qc, obs])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "obs = SparsePauliOp(\"ZZ\")\n",
    "job = backend.run(qc, obs mode=\"estimator\")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "obs = SparsePauliOp(\"ZZ\")\n",
    "estimator = Estimator(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = estimator.run(qc, obs)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "obs = SparsePauliOp(\"ZZ\")\n",
    "job = backend.run([qc, obs], mode=\"estimator\")\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "57c2a77448a9ccb3"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "obs = SparsePauliOp(\"ZZ\")\n",
    "estimator = Estimator(backend=backend)\n",
    "job = estimator.run([qc, obs])\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "7f6004e5630c2bc5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "5bc0b90fa0706509"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**18. Given a `estimator` instance, how would you enable Zero Noise Estimation and Twirling Readout Error Extinction (T-REx) options?**",
   "id": "6705f22ae6dd476e"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "estimator.options.resilience.zne_mitigation = True\n",
    "estimator.options.resilience.measure_mitigation = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "B)\n",
    "```\n",
    "estimator.resilience.zne_mitigation = True\n",
    "estimator.resilience.measure_mitigation = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "C)\n",
    "```\n",
    "estimator.zne_mitigation = True\n",
    "estimator.measure_mitigation = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "D)\n",
    "```\n",
    "estimator.options.zne_mitigation = True\n",
    "estimator.options.measure_mitigation = True\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "eb7f3d2d8c87994f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A)\n",
    "```\n",
    "estimator.options.resilience.zne_mitigation = True\n",
    "estimator.options.resilience.measure_mitigation = True\n",
    "```\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "ddf30906858aebdd"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "e86d820984bd42da"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**19. Given an `EstimatorResult` object `results`, how do you retrieve the expectation values?**",
   "id": "1b6f0e5759d4f73a"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) `evs = results.data.evs`\n",
    "\n",
    "B) `evs = results[0].data.evs`\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `evs = results.evs`\n",
    "\n",
    "D) `evs = results[0].evs`\n"
   ],
   "id": "7e0a838a167829e7"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "B) `evs = results[0].data.evs`\n",
    "\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "b686dafc1da383cd"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "7fd3afff40135b15"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**20. Given a `service` instance and a `job_id`, how do you retrieve the corresponding job?**\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "A) `retrieved_job = service.job(job_id)`\n",
    "\n",
    "B) `retrieved_job = service.from_id(job_id)`\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `retrieved_job = service.jobs[job_id]`\n",
    "\n",
    "D) `retrieved_job = service.find_job(job_id)`"
   ],
   "id": "b10aad3f3a9f7ada"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "A) `retrieved_job = service.job(job_id)`\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "b00c6e9e11477819"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "9b22eb47a758411b"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**21. What is the behavior of `job.result()` if the job has not yet finished executing when this line is reached?**\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "job = sampler.run([(isa_circuit, params)])\n",
    "...\n",
    "results = job.result()\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "318a7e674fd6b56f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) An error is raised, but the job continues running in the background.\n",
    "\n",
    "B) An error is raised and the job is aborted.\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `results` is assigned `None` until the job completes.\n",
    "\n",
    "D) `job.result()` blocks execution until the job finishes and the result is available."
   ],
   "id": "78c755b8a27a68f0"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "D) `job.result()` blocks execution until the job finishes and the result is available.\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "b190f714e73b9c11"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "8df63d280cb70baf"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**22. Why will the following code fail to export the quantum circuit `qc`?**\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "with open(\"qasm_file.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    dumps(qc, f)\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "7714a731d615c1d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) QASM files can only be exported to `.json` files.\n",
    "\n",
    "B) An `Exporter` instance must be created first, from which the `dumps` method should be called.\n",
    "\n",
    "C) The syntax is incorrect, it should be `f.dumps(qc)`.\n",
    "\n",
    "D) The syntax is wrong, `dump(qc, f)` should be used to export to a file."
   ],
   "id": "7bdc1b49619e7bf5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "D) The syntax is wrong, `dump(qc, f)` should be used to export to a file.\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "dc3afa2d90c4d3bb"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "fd23780d5675fc3d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "**23. After calling `response = requests.post(url, data=data)`, how do you verify that the request was successful?**\n",
    "\n",
    "A) `assert response[\"status_code\"] == True`\n",
    "\n",
    "B) `assert response[\"status_code\"] == 200`\n",
    "\n",
    "C) `assert response.status_code == 200`\n",
    "\n",
    "D) `assert response.status_code == True`"
   ],
   "id": "c6e90ffbdeb45864"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C) `assert response.status_code == 200`\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "cedd002679f2e6fa"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "1856e8f05dd47f8d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "**24. Where do you obtain the bearer token used for authenticating requests to the Qiskit Runtime REST API?**",
   "id": "ce53d8e54f6c555d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "A) The bearer token is the same as the API key.\n",
    "\n",
    "B) The bearer token is the CRN token.\n",
    "\n",
    "C) Submit a request to the REST API with your API key to obtain a bearer token.\n",
    "\n",
    "D) The bearer token is the IAM ID."
   ],
   "id": "9e3cf135b90ff348"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "***Answer:***\n",
    "<Details>\n",
    "<br/>\n",
    "C) Submit a request to the REST API with your API key to obtain a bearer token.\n",
    "</Details>"
   ],
   "id": "c3c46129ab63173"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "---",
   "id": "59626594172b381e"
  }
